# SOL Action Schema
# Defines the structure for actions that SOL can execute

{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "intent": {
      "type": "string",
      "enum": [
        "update_state",
        "log_event",
        "trigger_unity_signal",
        "append_to_note",
        "mark_session",
        "altar_pulse",
        "dojo_effect"
      ],
      "description": "The type of action to perform"
    },
    "field": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "The field to update (for update_state actions)"
    },
    "value": {
      "description": "The value to set (for update_state actions)"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Additional data for the action"
    }
  },
  "required": ["intent"],
  "additionalProperties": false
}

## Action Types

### update_state
Updates a field in the state.json file.
- field: The state field to update
- value: The new value

### log_event
Logs an event to memory.
- data: Event data to log

### trigger_unity_signal
Triggers a signal in the Unity Dojo environment.
- data: Signal parameters

### append_to_note
Appends content to an Obsidian note.
- data: { "note_path": "path/to/note.md", "content": "text to append" }

### mark_session
Marks the current session with metadata.
- data: Session metadata

### altar_pulse
Triggers an altar pulse in the Dojo.
- data: Pulse parameters

### dojo_effect
Applies an effect to a Dojo node.
- data: { "node": "altar", "effect": "glow", "duration": 30 }